5 Subject: Health; hospitals; hospital budgets; Green Mountain Care Board;
6 executive compensation; administrative staffing ratios
7 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to require
8 hospitals to provide information about employee compensation and
9 administrative staffing ratios to the Green Mountain Care Board as part of the
10 Board’s hospital budget review process and to make current compensation
11 information available to the Board throughout the year. The bill would also
12 direct the Board to ensure that the ratio of administrative employees at each
13 hospital to employees delivering health care services directly to patients is
14 aligned with national averages for similar hospitals and that the compensation
15 for a hospital’s executive and clinic leadership does not equal more than 10
16 times that of the hospital’s lowest-paid employees who deliver health care
17 services directly to hospital patients.
